What is CRM?

CRM (Customer Relationship Management) is used to manage:

👥 Customers
📞 Leads (potential customers)
💼 Opportunities (customers interested in buying)
📧 Follow-ups
💰 Sales Pipeline
📊 Sales Forecast
Real-world Example

Suppose you own an AI business.

| Customer                   | Requirement      | CRM Stage |
| -------------------------- | ---------------- | --------- |
| ABC Technologies           | Wants AI Website | Lead      |
| They requested a quotation | Opportunity      |           |
| They accepted quotation    | Won              |           |
| They rejected              | Lost             |           |


===
CRM helps you remember:

Who contacted you
What they need
When to call them
Whether they purchased

========
The stages are:

New → New inquiry received
Qualified → Customer is interested
Proposition → Quotation sent
Won → Customer purchased
Lost (hidden on the right) → Customer did not purchase

Each card is called an Opportunity.

